[This has been an ongoing problem, as the article indicates. It is
very sad the animals are being lost over a bacterial disease that does
not seem to present itself for easy control, or that it is being
brought to the bighorn sheep by domestic sheep.

While reestablishing the herd was important, one wonders now if doing
more homework on interactions with domestic sheep should have occurred
1st. - Mod.TG]
